Actress Zenande Mfenyana confronts cyber bullies who have been making her pregnancy hard. The seasoned actress took to Instagram to finally address what people have been saying about her looks. The The Queen actress has been getting comments about how she looks since getting pregnant. She said it's mostly women who make mean remarks. She posted multiple Instagram stories telling people to unfollow her if they are offended by the way she looks. She wrote: "If my big preggy nose and dark neck and whatever else you find repulsive about my preggy body offends you so much, then why are you following me?" After venting, she shared other messages that she received from women are went through the same thing she is going through. Read:Â RAPPER CASSPER NYOVEST TO BE A DAD! 